Half of the countries teachers didn't choose teaching as their first-choice career. That's according to the Teaching and Learning International Survey. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Half of the countries teachers didn't choose teaching as their first-choice career. That's according to the Teaching and Learning International Survey (TALIS). WATCH: Basic Education Minister reveals Talis results One of the report's authors, says it's important for teachers to be invested in the social mission of their profession. “In SA teaching was only the first choice of half the teachers. Lowest out of all Talis country. 66% is the average. Motivation is not only statistic, it matters really for later education. Teachers are more invested in the social mission of the profession tend to participate more in professional development activities,” said TALIS researcher and education expert Dr Markus Schwabe.